          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJRBoDX5WwCmZmhZejIwMM7o7r0QYtaiNtwMLSwrLfkoXYF_g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "Count your pills, make sure you received all of it when you pickup your prescription! I have been using this pharmacy for almost a decade, and had mostly good experiences before the last one, when I received 34 pills missing from a bottle of 90.\n\nFor several years I only had great experiences with this pharmacy, then a couple years ago I encountered one pharmacist with very unprofessional behavior, it happened a few times, but he isn\u2019t working there often. One time he dared to scold me, snapped at me telling me to \u201cput the phone down when you\u2019re talking to me\u201d as I was looking for the details of my prescription from my medical chart on my phone. I didn\u2019t complained about him to management or write a review then. I should have. There were no witnesses, I didn\u2019t have time to record the conversation.\n\nHowever, on October 6th of this year, something more seriously wrong took place. I just realized it recently. The prescription for my son\u2019s anxiety had a slight change in quantity, instead of having a refill every 30 days, now we get to have 90 days between refills. On October 6th, my husband picked up the prescription that had 34 pills missing from 90! We just ran out of it today, instead of January 5th, so we were facing 34 days without the SSRI anxiety medication that my son with severe special needs requires. He has severe meltdowns without it.\nLuckily his doctor sent a new prescription for this medication, after I reached out to her in panic, but our insurance refused to pay for it. We are on Medicaid and on public assistance. Cannot afford the burden to have to pay for the needed prescription full price. Why do we have to sacrifice when one of this pharmacy\u2019s employee stole one third of our medicine during or after the bottle refill?! There\u2019s no accountability, the other pharmacist I asked told just ignored my concerns. Yes, it wasn\u2019t him who stole, it was someone else, a crook, maybe that rude one I occasionally encountered before, maybe it is the same as the other reviewers mentioned.",
